<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870529-0132 </DOCNO><HL> Macmillan Inc. CompletesIts Acquisition of Publisher</HL><DD> 05/29/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> MLLBUYBACKS, REDEMPTIONS, SWAP OFFERS (BBK)TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> NEW YORK  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Macmillan Inc. completed the acquisition of Laidlaw Educational Publishers from Doubleday andamp; Co.    Terms weren't disclosed.    The acquisition of Laidlaw, a River Forest, Ill., publisher of elementary and secondary school books, provides Macmillan &quot;with additional growth opportunities in the elementary and high school textbook publishing market,&quot; said Edward P. Evans, chairman and chief executive officer of the publishing and information-services concern. He said Laidlaw is expected to &quot;contribute incremental earnings in 1987 and future years.&quot;    Doubleday, based here, was acquired last year by Bertelsmann AG of West Germany.    Separately, Macmillan said it called for redemption July 10 $75 million of 7 1/2% convertible debentures due July 1, 2010, at $1,060 per $1,000 of debentures. Each $1,000 of debentures is convertible through July 3 into 23.95 common shares, valued at about $1,400 at current prices.    In composite trading on the New York Stock Exchange, Macmillan common closed at $59.125, up $1.875. </TEXT></DOC>